            <Description>The DWP particle correlator data sets provide the result of the onboard autocorrelation
                of the PEACE HEEA count rate. Due to telemetry restrictions, only two of the possible 16 correlator 
                energy channels are returned. One data set, PCOR_FX provides AutoCorrelation Functions (ACFs) 
                at a fixed energy whilst the other 
                PCOR_ST data set (this file) steps through the remaining energy steps at a rate of one step per spin. 
                The 32 ACF lag values provide count rate information in the range 1.4-41.6kHz at a particular energy. 
                In normal mode, one ACF is produced every spin where as in burst modes there may be either 4, 8, or 
                16 ACFs per spin depending upon the WEC operational mode implemented. In addition to the ACF and energy, 
                this data set also contains the HEEA polar sensor from which the data were collected, the azimuth of 
                observations (BM only), the maximum and minimum pitch angles of the electrons recorded and an estimate 
                of the count rate based on the ACF. For further details, the user is referred to the DWP User Manual, 
                available from CSA, which contains a complete description of all parameters within the data set as well 
                as a list of the general caveats that apply to this data set. Note: Operation of the correlator in 
                normal mode ended on 2013-09-10.
            </Description>
